    Scope and Contents
Records of the University Hearing Board (1970-) including correspondence, minutes, reports, memoranda, and working papers with case files grievances heard by the board.  Major cases include 1973 Tenure Case (also called the Faculty Six), the 1975 Ron Ettinger Case, the 1975 Walter Kimmel Case, the 1976 Redge Ranyard Case, and the 1976 Steve Murov Case.  Other appeals have included Nathalie O. Funk, Phil Gekas, Larry Golden and Harold Kerster.  
  
    Arrangement Note
Filing of UHB, then case file, then larger cases arranged chronologically  
  
    Source of Acquisition
John Syer, Chair (1972-1074); James Worthy  
  
    Method of Acquisition
Piecemeal and from various cases  
